<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,152,179]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Leaf mine.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chambers, V. T." box="[293,505,153,179]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="54 - 58" refId="ref12839" refString="Chambers, V. T. (1871 a) Micro-lepidoptera. The Canadian Entomologist, 3, 54 - 58." type="journal article" year="1871">Chambers (1871a)</bibRefCitation>
described the characteristic upper-surface mine of this species (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1394,153,180]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. Phyllonorycter tiliacella. 68: Occupied leaf mine on Tilia americana; 69: Vacated mine with pupal exuviae protruding at right; 70: Reared adult." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713001/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs. 68–69</figureCitation>
) as follows: “Small, circular or ovate, brownish, mottled with whitish; not visible underneath until the lower cuticle dies.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Braun, A. F." box="[223,373,225,251]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" pagination="269 - 357" refId="ref12540" refString="Braun, A. F. (1908) Revision of the North American species of the genus Lithocolletis Hubner. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 34, 269 - 357. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 17825" type="journal article" year="1908">Braun (1908)</bibRefCitation>
characterized it as “white, densely speckled with dark brown”, which is in agreement with our observations.
</paragraph>
